### Hadith 3:214

*Narrated Ziyad bin Jubair:*

A man went to Ibn 'Umar I. and said, "A man vowed to fast one day (the
sub-narrator thinks that he said that the day was Monday), and that day
happened to be 'Id day." Ibn 'Umar said, "Allah orders vows to be
fulfilled and the Prophet forbade the fasting on this day (i.e. Id)."

